'let' do not hoist like 'var'
'let' scoped on 'for' loops despite outside curly-braces
'let' on 'for' loops sets an isolated scope every iteration
'const' do not let reassign the reference but the inner props still mutable
'const' use block scope
'=>' are not new-able as es5
'=>' has no arguments object
'=>' are different from 'functions'
'destructuring' object seems ugly, ask when developing with others
spread operator '...array' to destruct elements of an array
'string templates' ask when developing with others
'tags on string templates' ask when developing with others
beware of non-standard unicode characters on loops
